src: Dating back to the middle Ages, but believed to date from the Roman Empire and considering the ancient tradition of wine growing in this land, the first official recognition that makes the wine from La Mancha as an appellation of origin dates from 1932, published in “La Gaceta de Madrid” (today’s Governments State Gazette) in September of that year, making this DESIGNATION OF ORIGIN – DO one of the oldest in Spain. Subsequently, the Civil War and the difficult years of the war makes this project stand strong until the 60’s, when creating the PDO “La Mancha”, “Manchuela”, “Méntrida” and “Almansa”. Later, in 1973, began its journey in the Control Board, acquiring its own identity, culminating in 1976 with the Ministerial Order approving the first regulation of the DESIGNATION OF ORIGIN – DO and its Regulatory Board – OM.
mt: 追溯到中世纪，但被认为可以追溯到罗马帝国，并考虑到葡萄酒生长在这片土地上的古老传统，第一次官方承认来自拉曼查的葡萄酒为原产地名称可以追溯到1932年，并于当年9月发表在“La Gaceta de Madrid”（今天的政府国家公报）上，使这一原产地名称成为西班牙最古老的名称之一。随后，内战和战争的艰难岁月使这个项目一直坚持到60年代，当时创建了PDO“La Mancha”、“Manchuela”、“Méntrida”和“Almansa”。后来，在1973年，在控制委员会开始了它的旅程，获得了自己的身份，并在1976年随着部长命令批准原产地指定的第一个条例——DO及其管理委员会——OM而达到高潮。
